Excellent dish overall, if a bit oily. The flavors blend well, and none are overwhelming. Sophisticated enough for an adult palate, yet my two year-old asked for thirds! To cut the preparation time a bit, I used a Le Creuset Dutch oven in which I could brown all the chicken at once. I think this also cut the cooking time a bit (to 20 min. instead of 25-30) since it's a bit wider than the 12-inch skillet called for. I've only made this once, with that adjustment, but I don't see how all that food and sauce would fit in such a small skillet. The Le Creuset worked nicely. [Side dish note: I paired this with Aromatic Yellow Rice from Madhur Jaffrey's Indian Cooking (rice, tumeric, bay leaves, cinnamon stick, a little butter, whole cloves, golden raisins added), and it was a nice match.] I'd definitely make this again, especially for a weekend meal or for dinner guests. Very, very good!

