Rating: 4
ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS! I followed this recipe exact, except I placed the sauted carrots and onion with drippings into a large baking dish, then placed the frying pan browned chicken thighs on top, followed by pouring the lemon/water /honey liquid over, then covered with foil and baked in 350* for an hour. The last 15 minutes, without the foil, it made the skin semi-crisp and tacky from the honey! I then made my famous red, skin on, butter/cream/herb mashed potatoes and served the chicken/carrots and the gravy on top! We really enjoyed this dish, I will be making it again. The only downside to this recipe/cooking method...the frying...it's terribly messy. Definitely use a frying screen if you've got one!

