Everybody is right about this recipe, it is worth keeping and to share with casual company. I made a few modifications, as per some others suggestions: - used 2 large onions - added dried plums - to compensate for the swelling of the dried plums, I also increased the volume of water from 1/2 c. to 1/2 c. plus 2 Tbsp, and lemon juice volume from 1/4 c. to 1/3 c. - added finely minced lemon zest during the last minute of cooking. Serve Basmati or some type of Couscous instead of potatoes. Start with a Spinach, Grapefruit and Almond salad. Finish with a simple lemon tart (or Lemon Gelato). Wine: Alsatian Tokay-Pinot Gris, Autralian premium Shiraz

